import math
def r(n):
 cycle = 60
 index = (1 << len(bin(n))-3) % cycle
 cur = 0
 next = 1 
 for i in range(1, index):
  nextNext = (cur + next) % 10
  cur = next
  next = nextNext
 return cur

def fib(n):
 index = -1
 while n > 0:
  index += 1
  n = n // 2
 return index
